# Platform Profile: Grok (xAI)

**Provider:** xAI (Elon Musk)  
**Current Flagship:** Grok 4.20 / Grok 4.1 Fast  
**Interface:** grok.com, X (Twitter) integration, Grok Studio, API

---

## Strengths
- Real-time X (Twitter) data access — unique among frontier models
- Social signal intelligence: trending topics, public sentiment, real-time discourse
- 2M token context window (Grok 4.1 Fast)
- Grok Studio: canvas-style environment for code and document editing
- Agent Tools API for orchestrating external tools including web search and code execution
- Strong coding performance — competes with Claude and GPT on benchmarks
- Less filtered/more direct personality — useful for tasks where corporate caution creates friction
- Cost-competitive, especially for users already on X Premium

## Weaknesses
- Less refined instruction-following than Claude for complex structured tasks
- Prose quality below Claude for long-form writing
- Smaller ecosystem than OpenAI or Google
- Social/real-time data strength is a narrow differentiator for many use cases
- Enterprise adoption and governance tooling less mature than M365 Copilot or ChatGPT Enterprise

## Context Window
- Grok 4.1 Fast: 2M tokens
- Behavior: Large context handling is a genuine strength; well-suited for bulk document ingestion

## Memory & Persistence
- No persistent cross-session memory by default
- Grok Studio maintains canvas state within a session
- **Handoff note:** No native Projects equivalent — include full context in the prompt; use large context window to carry session state

## System Prompt Support
- ✅ API: full system prompt support
- ⚠️ Consumer interface: limited system prompt configuration
- Works well with role-framing in the first user message if system prompt isn't available

## Tool Availability
- X (Twitter) real-time data (native, unique)
- Web search (native)
- Code execution
- Agent Tools API (external tool orchestration)
- Grok Studio (code + document canvas)
- Image understanding

## Prompt Format Conventions
- Responds well to direct, conversational prompts
- Less dependent on XML or markdown structure than Claude
- For large context tasks: provide documents inline — 2M window handles bulk well
- For social/market research: frame as a monitoring brief with specific signals to track
- Grok Studio prompts: treat like a canvas instruction — describe the output artifact, not just the task

## Ideal Task Types
- Real-time social sentiment and trend monitoring
- X/Twitter signal analysis for market or brand intelligence
- Large document corpus analysis (where 2M context is needed)
- Competitive intelligence that requires current public discourse
- Coding tasks for users who are already in the X/Grok ecosystem
- Tasks where a less filtered, more direct response is useful
- Cost-sensitive workloads where Grok's pricing is competitive

